ZH: 他们打算闹革命推翻现政府。
EN: They plan to start a revolution to overthrow the current government.

ZH: 这个国家的人民不满现状，开始闹革命。
EN: The people of this country are dissatisfied with the status quo and have started a revolution.

ZH: 他参加了一场闹革命的游行。
EN: He participated in a protest as part of the revolution.

ZH: 一群年轻人开始闹革命，要求政府做出改变。
EN: A group of young people started a revolution, demanding changes from the government.

ZH: 他们正在闹革命，要求更多民主权利。
EN: They are in the midst of a revolution, demanding more democratic rights.

ZH: 这个国家的青少年是这次闹革命的主要推动力。
EN: The youth of this country are the main driving force behind this revolution.

ZH: 他没有想到这次抗议会演变成一场闹革命的运动。
EN: He didn't expect this protest to turn into a full-blown revolution.

ZH: 他被指控煽动人民闹革命。
EN: He was accused of inciting people to start a revolution.

ZH: 他们试图用暴力手段闹革命，但被阻止了。
EN: They tried to start a revolution through violent means, but were stopped.

ZH: 一些人认为闹革命是最后的选择。
EN: Some people believe that starting a revolution is the last resort.

ZH: 他们的目的不只是闹革命，更是要为人民谋求更好的生活。
EN: Their goal is not just to start a revolution, but to seek a better life for the people.

ZH: 这次闹革命给政府带来了很大压力。
EN: This revolution has put a lot of pressure on the government.

ZH: 大家都在为这场闹革命做准备。
EN: Everyone is preparing for the revolution.

ZH: 他们希望这次闹革命能为国家带来积极的改变。
EN: They hope that this revolution will bring positive changes to the country.

ZH: 那个革命领袖能把人们团结在一起，一起闹革命。
EN: That revolutionary leader was able to unite people and start a revolution together.

ZH: 他们相信只有通过闹革命才能改变现状。
EN: They believe that only by starting a revolution can they change the current situation.

ZH: 很多人加入了这场闹革命的行动。
EN: Many people have joined the revolution movement.

ZH: 一部分人认为闹革命是非常危险的做法。
EN: Some people think starting a revolution is a very dangerous move.

